## 5. Framework System Identifiers

Each framework has a system identifier used as `gen_ai.provider.name` on framework-level spans:

| Framework | `gen_ai.provider.name` | Constant Name | npm Package |
|-----------|----------------------|---------------|-------------|
| LangChain | `langchain` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_LANGCHAIN` | `@langchain/core` |
| LangGraph | `langgraph` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_LANGGRAPH` | `@langchain/langgraph` |
| OpenAI Agents | `openai` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_OPENAI` | `@openai/agents` |
| Mastra | `mastra` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_MASTRA` | `@mastra/core` |
| Claude Agents SDK | `claude_agent_sdk` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_CLAUDE_AGENT_SDK` | `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` |
| Google ADK | `google_adk` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_GOOGLE_ADK` | `@google/adk` |
| Strands Agents | `strands_agents` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_STRANDS` | `@strands-agents/sdk` |
| LlamaIndex | `llama_index` | `GEN_AI_SYSTEM_LLAMAINDEX` | `llamaindex` |

**IMPORTANT**: OpenAI Agents uses `openai` (not `openai_agents`) as `gen_ai.provider.name` on processor spans, matching Python. The `openai_agents` value is used for the framework system identifier in constants but the processor spans use `openai` since it's the underlying provider.

