## 9. Events in Framework Instrumentations

### LLM Chat Events
When a framework handles LLM chat calls (e.g., LangChain `handleLLMEnd`), emit inference events the same way provider instrumentations do:

```typescript
OpenLitHelper.emitInferenceEvent(span, {
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_OPERATION]: 'chat',
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_REQUEST_MODEL]: requestModel,
  [SemanticConvention.GEN_AI_RESPONSE_MODEL]: responseModel,
  // ... all standard inference event attributes
});
```

### Non-LLM Spans
Framework spans (`invoke_agent`, `invoke_workflow`, `execute_tool`) typically do NOT emit inference events (matching Python behavior). Only `chat`-type spans within the framework emit events.

---

## 10. Metrics in Framework Instrumentations

### LLM Chat Metrics
When a framework handles LLM chat calls, record metrics via `BaseWrapper.recordMetrics()` the same way provider instrumentations do. This includes token usage, duration, cost, TTFT/TBT for streaming.

### Framework Operation Metrics
For non-LLM framework spans (workflow, agent, tool), record operation duration via the same metrics pattern but with framework-appropriate attributes.

---

## 11. Custom Attributes in Framework Instrumentations

Custom attributes MUST be applied to ALL framework spans (not just LLM spans), matching Python SDK behavior:

- `applyCustomSpanAttributes(span)` MUST be called on every `create_agent`, `invoke_agent`, `invoke_workflow`, `execute_tool`, and `chat` span
- Events emitted from framework instrumentations MUST include merged custom attributes via `getMergedCustomAttributes()`
- Metrics are NOT tagged with custom attributes (same as provider instrumentations)

---

## 12. Framework-Specific Handling When Framework Has Native Telemetry

When a framework already has OTel (Strands, Mastra) or custom tracing (OpenAI Agents):

### Skip LLM Span Types (OpenAI Agents)
The processor MUST skip SDK span types that correspond to LLM calls (e.g., `response`, `generation`), letting the provider instrumentation (OpenAI) handle those:
```typescript
const LLM_SPAN_TYPES = new Set(['response', 'generation']);
if (LLM_SPAN_TYPES.has(spanType)) return; // skip, let provider handle
```

### Enrich Existing Spans (Strands, Mastra)
The SpanProcessor enriches framework-created spans with OpenLIT attributes:
- `on_start`: Set OpenLIT metadata (sdk.name, environment, service.name), apply custom attributes
- `on_end`: Normalize attributes, extract content from span events, emit inference events, record metrics

### Detect Framework Spans
For SpanProcessor-based instrumentations, detect relevant spans by:
- Instrumentation scope name (e.g., `strands.telemetry.tracer`)
- `gen_ai.system` or `gen_ai.provider.name` attribute value
- Span name patterns (e.g., starts with `agent.`)

---

## 13. File Structure

Each framework instrumentation follows this structure:

```
sdk/typescript/src/instrumentation/{framework-name}/
  index.ts      # InstrumentationNodeModuleDefinition, patch/unpatch
  wrapper.ts    # Span creation, attribute setting, event/metric emission
```

For SpanProcessor-based instrumentations:
```
sdk/typescript/src/instrumentation/{framework-name}/
  index.ts      # Registers processor with TracerProvider
  processor.ts  # SpanProcessor or TracingProcessor implementation
  utils.ts      # Span name generation, attribute helpers
```

---

## 14. Registration

Each new framework instrumentation MUST be registered in:

1. **`sdk/typescript/src/types.ts`**: Add to `InstrumentationType` union
2. **`sdk/typescript/src/instrumentation/index.ts`**: Import and add to `availableInstrumentations`
3. **`sdk/typescript/src/semantic-convention.ts`**: Add system constants and any new attribute constants

